CSS User Interface

CSS User Interface property allows us to change the element into one of the several standard user interface elements.

Following are some properties which we use in CSS User Interface :-
1.  Box-Sizing - It allows the users to fix elements on area.
2.  Appearance - It is used to allow the user to make elements as user interface elements.
3.  Resize     - It is basically used to resize the element present on the area.
4.  Icon       - It provides the icon on the area.
5.  Nav-down   - It is used to move down when we pressed on down arrow button in keypad.
6.  Nav-left   - It is used to move left when we pressed on left arrow button in keypad.
7.  Nav right  - It is used to move right when we pressed on right arrow button in keypad.
8.  Nav-up     - It is used to move up when we pressed on up arrow button in keypad.

Let's see the examples of Resizing property:-

Resizing Property have three common values as bsj=hown n=below-
   • Horizontal
   • Vertical
   • Both Horizontal and Vertical
   
Code example implementing both Horizontal and vertical property in CSS3 User Interface :-
  <html>
      <head>
      <style>
         div {
            border: 1px solid;
            padding: 15px; 
            width: 200px;
            resize: both;
            overflow: auto;
         }
      </style>
   </head>

   <body>
      <div>Heroku.com</div>
   </body>
</html>
